    "introduction": "\"黄凯，影视导演和监制，1983年生于上海，上海大学上海电影学院编导专业毕业，美国南加大-上科大制片人专业进修。黄凯制作并导演的首部院线电影《上海公园》于2009年上映，入围莫斯科、台北、科隆等10余个国际电影节。黄凯的工作领域也同时覆盖广告和电视剧。2016年黄凯执导剧集《陈二狗的妖孽人生》（第一季、第二季）；2020年，黄凯监制并导演的网络剧《皮肤之下》问世。从悬疑到都市，他的作品跨越多种不同类型。截至今日黄凯导演或监制的各类影视作品已在全球40余电影节展映，荣获超过30个奖项。\\r\\n\\r\\nBorn and bred in Shanghai, China, graduated from Shanghai Film Academy, Huang Kai Kevin (H.K.K.) made his big screen debut “Park Shanghai” (2009) at the age of 23. The film premiered at 30th Moscow Film Festival before theatrical release in China in 2009. Kai also works for TVC, documentary, short films and TV series. In 2015, he directed series drama “The Curious Journey of Chen Er-Gou” (2016), hitting 1.6 billion clicks soon after it’s on air. In 2018, he produced and directed series “Life under My Skin” (2020). With his own unique perspective, Kai explores the spiritual dimensions of his characters. By working on a variety of genres of productions, H.K.K. has developed a strong personal style of story-telling, winning him over 30 awards worldwide in his film career up until now.\"",
